JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s headline consumer inflation rose slightly more than expected to 5.4% year-on-year in May from 5.3% in April, data from Statistics South Africa showed on Wednesday, further weakening the rand.Economists polled by Reuters had forecast a 5.3% year-on-year inflation print.On a month-on-month basis inflation also inched higher, to 0.3% in May from 0.1% previously.Core inflation, which excludes the prices of food, non-alcoholic beverages, petrol and energy, was flat 4.8% year-on-year in May, the same figure as in April, while on a month-on-month basis the rate fell to 0.1% in May from 0.2% in April. 